# Build-context whitelist for `.docker/Dockerfile.ci`.
#
# The image build (.github/workflows/build-ci-image.yml) sends the
# project root as Docker build context. Without this file, the
# context includes `mcp-server-haskell/dist-newstyle/` (cabal's
# build artefacts, often >1 GB), `.git/` (history, ~100 MB), and
# the docs/ tree — none of which the Dockerfile's COPY needs.
#
# Effect: faster context upload to the Docker daemon and smaller
# layer inputs. On a cold image build, this trims ~30-60 s off
# the "transferring context" step.

# Build artefacts — cabal v2 produces these at runtime; the image
# builds its own from scratch.
**/dist-newstyle/
**/dist-newstyle-mcp/
**/dist/

# Git history is not needed inside the image. Unconditional
# exclusion: even with --no-git below, having the .git tree in
# the build context bloats the upload by tens of MB.
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Docs are not needed in the CI image. Trim them out to keep the
# context surface focused on what the Dockerfile actually copies.
docs/
*.pdf
*.md

# Local developer scratch + IDE state.
.claude/
.haskell-flows/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# CI configuration — referenced by the workflow but not consumed
# inside the image build itself.
.github/

# Nix outputs.
result
result-*
.direnv/

# Releases + temporary tarballs.
mcp-server-haskell/_release/
mcp-server-haskell/_release_assets/
*.tar.gz
*.tar
